nal day, the moments that will live long in the memory of fans came during the games' action-packed two weeks.\", \"from\": 533, \"to\": 700, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 551}, {\"ngram\": \"the attention\", \"from\": 567, \"to\": 580}, {\"ngram\": \"the final day\", \"from\": 584, \"to\": 597}, {\"ngram\": \"the moments\", \"from\": 599, \"to\": 610}, {\"ngram\": \"the memory\", \"from\": 634, \"to\": 644}, {\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 648, \"to\": 652}, {\"ngram\": \"the games' action-packed two weeks\", \"from\": 665, \"to\": 699}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Al Jazeera picks the top five viral moments and talking points from Paris 2024 that took the world by storm: In the weeks building up to Paris 2024, one athlete who dominated the headlines like no other was American gymnastSimone Biles.\", \"from\": 702, \"to\": 939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 702, \"end\": 712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"score\": 0.9999999446436065, \"rank\": 5.535099590171748e-08, \"text\": \"Al Jazeera\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\"}, {\"begin\": 770, \"end\": 780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1643751454224703e-20, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 840, \"end\": 850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1643751454224703e-20, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 910, \"end\": 918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999782289133483, \"rank\": 2.176535793984109e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the top five viral moments\", \"from\": 719, \"to\": 745}, {\"ngram\": \"talking points\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 764}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 791, \"to\": 800}, {\"ngram\": \"storm\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 809}, {\"ngram\": \"the weeks\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 823}, {\"ngram\": \"one athlete\", \"from\": 851, \"to\": 862}, {\"ngram\": \"the headlines\", \"from\": 877, \"to\": 890}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Arguably the greatest gymnast of all time with 11 Olympic medals to her name, Biles made a return that garnered attention after she abruptly pulled out of competition at the Tokyo Olympics three years ago.\", \"from\": 941, \"to\": 1146, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all time\", \"from\": 974, \"to\": 982}, {\"ngram\": \"11 Olympic medals\", \"from\": 988, \"to\": 1005}, {\"ngram\": \"her name\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1017}, {\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 1019, \"to\": 1024}, {\"ngram\": \"a return\", \"from\": 1030, \"to\": 1038}, {\"ngram\": \"attention\", \"from\": 1053, \"to\": 1062}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 1096, \"to\": 1107}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 1111, \"to\": 1129}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From her starry leotard emblazoned with crystals to her jaw-dropping performances in the heats, she inspired Bilesmania that took over the games.\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1293, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her starry leotard\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1171}, {\"ngram\": \"crystals\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1196}, {\"ngram\": \"her jaw-dropping performances\", \"from\": 1200, \"to\": 1229}, {\"ngram\": \"the heats\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1242}, {\"ngram\": \"Bilesmania\", \"from\": 1257, \"to\": 1267}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1292}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fans eagerly awaited her return to the limelight, and the world's most decorated gymnast did not disappoint.\", \"from\": 1295, \"to\": 1403, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Fans\", \"from\": 1295, \"to\": 1299}, {\"ngram\": \"her return\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1326}, {\"ngram\": \"the limelight\", \"from\": 1330, \"to\": 1343}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's most decorated gymnast\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 1383}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 27-year-old's nearly faultless routines in the women's team all-around final on July 30 brought the biggest celebrities to Bercy Arena in Paris and helped Team USA bag the gold medal that they lost in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1615, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1531, \"end\": 1542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bercy Arena\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\"}, {\"begin\": 1546, \"end\": 1551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.83302123614307e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1609, \"end\": 1614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.999980412429458, \"rank\": 1.9587954154171635e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 27-year-old's nearly faultless routines\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1447}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's team\", \"from\": 1451, \"to\": 1467}, {\"ngram\": \"all-around final\", \"from\": 1468, \"to\": 1484}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 1488, \"to\": 1492}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest celebrities\", \"from\": 1504, \"to\": 1527}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold medal\", \"from\": 1576, \"to\": 1590}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The self-proclaimed GOAT - Biles was seen wearing a necklace with a goat at its centre - went on to win gold in the individual all-around and vault finals.\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1772, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1637, \"end\": 1641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/GOAT_(platform)\", \"score\": 0.7168567345960191, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"GOAT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/GOAT_(platform)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/GOAT_(platform)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a necklace\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1677}, {\"ngram\": \"a goat\", \"from\": 1683, \"to\": 1689}, {\"ngram\": \"its centre\", \"from\": 1693, \"to\": 1703}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1721, \"to\": 1725}, {\"ngram\": \"all-around and vault finals\", \"from\": 1744, \"to\": 1771}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Shebaggedsilver in floor exercises and failed to qualify for the uneven bars final.\", \"from\": 1773, \"to\": 1856, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Shebaggedsilver\", \"from\": 1773, \"to\": 1788}, {\"ngram\": \"floor exercises\", \"from\": 1792, \"to\": 1807}, {\"ngram\": \"the uneven bars\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 1849}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The star capped off her stint in Tokyo by holding the Olympic flag during the closing ceremony as it was handed over from Paris to Los Angeles - where Biles may still turn up and steal the show once more.\", \"from\": 1858, \"to\": 2062, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1891, \"end\": 1896, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.999980412429458, \"rank\": 1.9587954154171635e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1980, \"end\": 1985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.83302123614307e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1989, \"end\": 2000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.71788854831464e-16, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The star\", \"from\": 1858, \"to\": 1866}, {\"ngram\": \"her stint\", \"from\": 1878, \"to\": 1887}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic flag\", \"from\": 1908, \"to\": 1924}, {\"ngram\": \"the closing ceremony\", \"from\": 1932, \"to\": 1952}, {\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 2009, \"to\": 2014}, {\"ngram\": \"the show\", \"from\": 2043, \"to\": 2051}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was hard to miss the aura of Turkey's pistol shooterYusuf Dikec.\", \"from\": 2066, \"to\": 2133, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2098, \"end\": 2104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"score\": 0.9922347994123673, \"rank\": 0.00782529058772709, \"text\": \"Turkey\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the aura\", \"from\": 2086, \"to\": 2094}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His hand-in-pocket shooting style not only brought him a team silver medal in the mixed team 10-metre (33-foot) air pistol final, it also shot the 51-year-old to instant fame on social media.\", \"from\": 2134, \"to\": 2325, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"pocket\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2152}, {\"ngram\": \"a team silver medal\", \"from\": 2189, \"to\": 2208}, {\"ngram\": \"the mixed team\", \"from\": 2212, \"to\": 2226}, {\"ngram\": \"instant fame\", \"from\": 2296, \"to\": 2308}, {\"ngram\": \"social media\", \"from\": 2312, \"to\": 2324}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Viral images showed Dikec shooting in a T-shirt with one hand in his pocket, a seemingly standard pair of glasses and an impassive look on his face.\", \"from\": 2327, \"to\": 2475, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Viral images\", \"from\": 2327, \"to\": 2339}, {\"ngram\": \"Dikec\", \"from\": 2347, \"to\": 2352}, {\"ngram\": \"a T-shirt\", \"from\": 2365, \"to\": 2374}, {\"ngram\": \"one hand\", \"from\": 2380, \"to\": 2388}, {\"ngram\": \"his pocket\", \"from\": 2392, \"to\": 2402}, {\"ngram\": \"a seemingly standard pair\", \"from\": 2404, \"to\": 2429}, {\"ngram\": \"glasses\", \"from\": 2433, \"to\": 2440}, {\"ngram\": \"an impassive look\", \"from\": 2445, \"to\": 2462}, {\"ngram\": \"his face\", \"from\": 2466, \"to\": 2474}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He gave off guy-next-door vibes and social media was all for it.\", \"from\": 2476, \"to\": 2540, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"guy-next-door vibes\", \"from\": 2488, \"to\": 2507}, {\"ngram\": \"social media\", \"from\": 2512, \"to\": 2524}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The social media fame prompted Dikec to set up an account on X, where he invited the platform's owner, Tesla and SpaceX CEO Elon Musk, to Istanbul to discuss the future of robots as shooters.\", \"from\": 2542, \"to\": 2733, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2645, \"end\": 2650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikola_Tesla\", \"score\": 0.9999223866573698, \"rank\": 7.761936698627995e-05, \"text\": \"Tesla\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikola_Tesla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikola_Tesla\"}, {\"begin\": 2655, \"end\": 2661, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SpaceX\", \"score\": 0.999999999992724, \"rank\": 7.489813773135199e-12, \"text\": \"SpaceX\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SpaceX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SpaceX\"}, {\"begin\": 2666, \"end\": 2675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elon Musk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\"}, {\"begin\": 2680, \"end\": 2688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Istanbul\", \"score\": 0.9999999971546458, \"rank\": 1.5011424716993546e-09, \"text\": \"Istanbul\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Istanbul\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Istanbul\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The social media fame\", \"from\": 2542, \"to\": 2563}, {\"ngram\": \"Dikec\", \"from\": 2573, \"to\": 2578}, {\"ngram\": \"an account\", \"from\": 2589, \"to\": 2599}, {\"ngram\": \"X\", \"from\": 2603, \"to\": 2604}, {\"ngram\": \"the platform's owner\", \"from\": 2623, \"to\": 2643}, {\"ngram\": \"the future\", \"from\": 2700, \"to\": 2710}, {\"ngram\": \"robots\", \"from\": 2714, \"to\": 2720}, {\"ngram\": \"shooters\", \"from\": 2724, \"to\": 2732}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Dikec's biggest and long-lasting impact was that on other athletes, who posed in his trademark shooting style after winning medals.\", \"from\": 2735, \"to\": 2875, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Dikec's biggest and long-lasting impact\", \"from\": 2744, \"to\": 2783}, {\"ngram\": \"other athletes\", \"from\": 2796, \"to\": 2810}, {\"ngram\": \"his trademark shooting style\", \"from\": 2825, \"to\": 2853}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 2868, \"to\": 2874}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From record-breaking men's pole vault gold medalist Armand Duplantis of Sweden to Australia's women's pole vault champion Nina Kennedy and many others, athletes far and wide performed the Dikec celebration during the final week.\", \"from\": 2877, \"to\": 3105, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2929, \"end\": 2945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armand_Duplantis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0